{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Chatbot CIC Compliance Check",
  "description": "Scans the current chatbot backend and verifies it meets all CIC requirements: CDK patterns, Lambda structure, Knowledge Base setup, Cognito auth, DynamoDB encryption, API Gateway config, IAM least privilege, and security standards.",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Perform a comprehensive CIC compliance check on the chatbot backend in this project. Scan all relevant files (backend/lib, backend/lambda, chatbots/**/lib, chatbots/**/lambda) and evaluate against the following requirements. Report PASS, FAIL, or WARNING for each item, then provide a prioritized fix list.\n\n## INFRASTRUCTURE (CDK Stack)\n- [ ] Knowledge Base: Uses Bedrock Knowledge Base (CfnKnowledgeBase or L2 construct). Check for knowledgeBaseId in Lambda env vars.\n- [ ] Vector Store: OpenSearch Serverless (VectorCollection + VectorIndex) or equivalent. Verify vectorDimensions match the embedding model.\n- [ ] Data Sources: At least one S3 or Web Crawler data source attached to the KB.\n- [ ] Embedding Model: Uses a valid Bedrock embedding model ARN (e.g., amazon.nova-2-multimodal-embeddings-v1:0 or titan-embed-text-v2).\n- [ ] Generation Model: Uses a cross-region inference profile (e.g., global.amazon.nova-2-lite-v1:0 or us.anthropic.claude-*) — NOT a direct model ARN.\n- [ ] Amplify: Frontend deployed via Amplify with GitHub source provider and build spec. CORS origins reference amplifyAppUrl, not hardcoded '*'.\n- [ ] API Gateway: REST API with CORS configured. Has DEFAULT_4XX and DEFAULT_5XX gateway responses with CORS headers.\n- [ ] Streaming: If streaming is used, Lambda uses Lambda Web Adapter layer or RESPONSE_STREAM invoke mode.\n- [ ] DynamoDB: All tables have encryption: dynamodb.TableEncryption.AWS_MANAGED or KMS. pointInTimeRecoveryEnabled: true on user/conversation tables. removalPolicy: RETAIN on production data tables.\n- [ ] S3 Buckets: enforceSSL: true on all buckets. blockPublicAccess configured (BLOCK_ALL unless public/ prefix is intentionally exposed via bucket policy).\n- [ ] Cognito: User Pool present for admin access. Identity Pool (if used) has minimal unauthenticated permissions.\n- [ ] Secrets: GitHub token stored in Secrets Manager, not passed as plain env var to Lambda.\n- [ ] Context Variables: Required context vars (githubToken, githubOwner, githubRepo) validated at stack init with a clear error message.\n\n## LAMBDA FUNCTIONS\n- [ ] Runtime: Python 3.12+ (3.13 preferred) for all Python Lambdas.\n- [ ] Handler pattern: Thin handler — lambda_handler(event, context) or handler(event, context) with minimal logic.\n- [ ] Type hints: All function signatures use Python type hints.\n- [ ] Error handling: All Bedrock API calls wrapped in try/except with specific exception types (ValidationException, ThrottlingException, AccessDeniedException, etc.).\n- [ ] CORS headers: All Lambda responses include Access-Control-Allow-Origin header.\n- [ ] Environment variables: KNOWLEDGE_BASE_ID, table names, and model IDs come from env vars — never hardcoded.\n- [ ] No PII in logs: print() statements do not log user queries, emails, or personal data.\n- [ ] Invoke KB Lambda: Uses bedrock-agent-runtime retrieve_and_generate or retrieve_and_generate_stream. Session ID passed through correctly.\n- [ ] Streaming Lambda (if present): Uses FastAPI or similar with Lambda Web Adapter. Conversation history saved to DynamoDB.\n\n## IAM & SECURITY\n- [ ] Least privilege: No Action: '*' or Resource: '*' in Lambda IAM policies (except where unavoidable for Bedrock model ARNs — flag these).\n- [ ] KB permissions: Lambda role has bedrock:RetrieveAndGenerate, bedrock:Retrieve, bedrock:InvokeModel scoped appropriately.\n- [ ] DynamoDB grants: Uses table.grantReadWriteData(fn) or table.grantReadData(fn) — not inline wildcard policies.\n- [ ] S3 grants: Uses bucket.grantRead(fn) or bucket.grantReadWrite(fn).\n- [ ] No hardcoded secrets: No API keys, tokens, or passwords in Lambda code or CDK stack.\n- [ ] Admin API: If admin endpoints exist, they are protected by Cognito authorizer or IAM auth — not open.\n\n## CHATBOT FUNCTIONALITY\n- [ ] Session management: sessionId passed to KB API for conversation continuity.\n- [ ] Citation handling: Citations from KB response are parsed and returned to frontend.\n- [ ] Feedback mechanism: Endpoint or mechanism exists to capture user feedback (positive/negative).\n- [ ] Language support: If multilingual, language parameter handled in Lambda.\n- [ ] Admin dashboard: If present, protected by Cognito and reads from conversation history table.\n\nAfter the scan, output:\n1. A summary table with PASS/FAIL/WARNING for each item\n2. A prioritized list of issues to fix (CRITICAL → HIGH → MEDIUM → LOW)\n3. Specific code snippets or CDK patterns to fix each FAIL item\n4. Reference the chatbots/backend_cincinnati pattern as the gold standard where applicable"
  },
  "workspaceFolderName": "Repository-Template",
  "shortName": "chatbot-cic-compliance-check"
}
